The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Orissa ties up with Uttam Galva Steels

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Bhubaneswar, Oct. 14: Secondary steel producer Uttam Galva Steels has teamed up with the Orissa government to set up a 3-million-tonne steel plant, a bicycle plant and a 210-megawatt captive power plant at an estimated investment of Rs 8,987 crore.

 Two companies, based in South Korea and the United Kingdom, will invest Rs 900 crore in the 3-million-tonne steel plant. 

 The company now has a production capacity of 1 million tonnes. 

 Uttam Galva Steels mostly manufactures and markets galvanised products, cold rolled coils, hot rolled coils and steel flats.

 Chairman and managing director R.K. Miglani signed the MoU with state steel and mines secretary L.N. Gupta yesterday. 

 The company is roping in a German collaborator for the Rs 150-crore bicycle unit to be located at Gopalpur town in Ganjam district. 




